The paper examines the references in elite publications, which are likely to be in the fields of computer science, information retrieval, digital libraries, cybersecurity, and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
